    "Inter-rater agreement for the MedQA GPT-3.5 evaluation was 97% with a Cohen's Kappa of 0.93.",
    "The GPT-4 API generated an error for 20 questions of the test set, reducing the test set size to 498.",
    "Overall, GPT-4 demonstrated improved accuracy over GPT-3.5.",
    "GPT-4 achieved an accuracy of 76% with traditional CoT, 77% with intuitive reasoning (+0.8%, CI -3.6% to +5.2%, p = 0.73), 78% with differential diagnosis (+2.2%, CI -2.3% to +6.7%, p = 0.24), 78% with analytic reasoning (+1.6%, CI -2.4% to +5.6%, p = 0.35), and 72% with Bayesian Inference (-3.4%, CI -9.1% to +1.2%, p = 0.07).",
    "Results can be found in Table 4."
